Key Match Events: Scottie Barnes had 33 points and 13 rebounds, leading the Toronto Raptors to a 130-113 victory over the Brooklyn Nets.
Immanuel Quickley returned after missing 22 games and added 21 points and 15 assists.
Gradey Dick contributed 22 points and three steals.
Brooklyn's D'Angelo Russell scored 22 points off the bench in his first game since being acquired in a trade with the Los Angeles Lakers.
Cameron Johnson scored 24 points for the Nets, while Keon Johnson finished with 17 points.
Nic Claxton had 16 points and 10 rebounds for Brooklyn.
Toronto led 94-91 after three quarters and started the fourth with a 10-4 surge to lead by nine with 8:22 to play.
Quickley's 3-pointer gave Toronto a 119-99 lead with 4:17 remaining.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Brooklyn's Noah Clowney fell on his back going for a rebound and went to the dressing room with 26 seconds left in the third quarter and did not return.
Brooklyn's Maxwell Lewis was helped off the court and taken to the dressing room after falling late in the fourth quarter.
Toronto's RJ Barrett (illness) and Bruce Brown (knee) and Brooklyn's Cam Thomas (hamstring) did not play.
